race.comment: PRINCE PAPA (8) returned in great order at Canberra in November and has been knocking on the door since. Is already a winner here, just needs some luck from the draw. LIGHTLY SPARKLED (7) never really looked likely fresh when settling towards the rear but was doing her best work late. Has never missed the placings at the second run back. Fitter so anticipating a better run this time. SANTOLINI (4) caused a blowout result last time at Goulburn when getting the job done. Deserves more respect this time. VAINSTREAM (5) has a moderate winning strike-rate but performed well last time at Queanbeyan, finishing second and only a long neck from the winner at the end of 1000m. Looks well placed so expect a bold display. SUPER SUNNY SEEYA (9) returns and has got the job done fresh before. Boasts a strong record over this journey and is drawn well for hot-hand hoop Boudvillain. Can return a winner.
